This was the first time I‚Äôve had fun with racing in a really long time even though it wasn‚Äôt exactly the result I wanted. One of my best friends on my high school cross country team, Gunnar Schultz, passed away in a car accident in November. Gunnar was always there to motivate me when I struggled in high school and was one of the best/selfless teammates someone could ever ask for (attaching screenshot of the last text he sent me). Tonight I got to wear my high school singlet in honor of him and I felt him with me through the whole race. I desperately miss him, but even now I know he‚Äôll always be here to pick me up when I‚Äôm down. 

Race details - coach wanted me to go really conservative at 9:00-9:05 through 3k and so I came through 3k at 9:02 but my group was really slowing down. Had to run alone the final 2k trying to catch the front pack but it was a massive grind. Confident that I can run a massive PR if I get into the right group and clock it off.

Alright now I‚Äôm really having fun with this sh*t again. Even wore the speedsuit for the meme. Goal was to conservatively bring the boys through the 1600m in 4:35 and was bang on.
